!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

club /klʌb/

(clubbing,clubbed,clubs) 

1. N-COUNT A club is an organization of people interested in a particular activity or subject who usually meet on a regular basis. 会社 

例： ...the Young Republicans Club. … 青年共和党会社。 

例： ...a youth club. …青年会社。 

2. N-COUNT A club is a place where the members of a club meet. 俱乐部 

例： I stopped in at the club for a drink. 我在俱乐部喝一杯歇歇脚。 

3. N-COUNT A club is a team which competes in sports competitions. 运动队 

例： ...the New York Yankees baseball club. …纽约扬基棒球队。 

4. N-COUNT A club is the same as a . 夜总会 

例： It's a big dance hit in the clubs. 在各个夜总会这可是个热门舞。 

5. N-COUNT A club is a long, thin, metal stick with a piece of wood or metal at one end that you use to hit the ball in golf. 高尔夫球棒 

例： ...a six-iron club. …一把6号铁头球棒。 

6. N-COUNT A club is a thick, heavy stick that can be used as a weapon. 棍棒 

例： Men armed with knives and clubs attacked his home. 一帮携刀带棍的人袭击了他的家。 

7. V-T To club a person or animal means to hit them hard with a thick heavy stick or a similar weapon. (用棍棒或类似武器) 狠打 

例： Two thugs clubbed him with baseball bats. 两名暴徒用棒球棍狠打了他。 

8. N-UNCOUNT-COLL Clubs is one of the four suits in a pack of playing cards. Each card in the suit is marked with one or more black symbols: ♣. (纸牌的) 梅花 

例： ...the ace of clubs. …梅花幺。 

9. N-COUNT A club is a playing card of this suit. (单张) 梅花 

例： The next player discarded a club. 接下来的那位玩家出了张梅花牌。

